== Why...? ==

Okay, this is probably an extremely stupid question (&quot;There are no stupid questions, just stupid people&quot;), but... ''why'' is it called &quot;Day of Thirst&quot;? Currently the article fails to explain... (or I'm missing the obvious.) -- [[User:Syzygy|Syzygy]] ([[User talk:Syzygy|talk]]) 08:01, 9 February 2012 (UTC)
:It is me rather than you who is at fault here, I neglected to mention the obvious ;). The Arab army suffered from thirst throughout the battle, and this is why the battle became known under this name. Al-Tabari even mentions an exhausted soldier snatching away Muslim ibn Sa'id's own water-cup to drink after the battle was over. [[User:Cplakidas|Constantine]]  [[User talk:Cplakidas| ‚úç ]] 15:30, 21 November 2013 (UTC)

